Havas, Air France, Klepierre, Vinci: French Equity Preview

-- B y   C a r o l   M a t l a c k   a n d   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i
-- 
2011-06-23T04:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-22/havas-air-france-klepierre-vinci-french-equity-preview.html
Shares in the following companies
may have unusual moves in Paris trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are from the last close.  France ’s CAC 40 Index fell 0.2 percent to 3,871.37. The
broader SBF 120 Index declined 0.2 percent to 2,921.14.  Havas SA (HAV)  : The French advertising company, which
has about $1 billion in cash that can be used in acquisitions,
prefers startups over a big takeover, Chief Executive Officer
 David Jones  said in an interview in Cannes. The shares fell 0.7
percent to 3.56 euros.  Air France SA (AF FP): Mechanics at the French airline
began a rolling strike, the CGT labor union said. The shares
fell 1 percent to 10.43 euros.  Klepierre (LI)  SA:  Europe ’s second-largest shopping-
center owner announced an agreement with Clear Channel France to
provide digital advertising displays in 73 French malls. The
shares slid 0.5 percent to 28.41 euros.  Vinci SA (DG)  : Europe’s largest construction group said
it signed a contract to build a new headquarters for SFR, the
mobile telecommunications unit of Vivendi SA, in the Paris
suburb of St. Denis. The shares fell 1.4 percent to 42.51 euros.  Prismaflex International (PRS)  SA: The billboard
designer and developer reported net earnings of 1.4 million
euros for the year ended March 31, up from a 0.35 million euros
loss a year earlier. The shares rose 2.5 percent to 12.89 euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carol Matlack in Paris at 
